      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">17/1/82 ¶  ¶ The last mail brought me the sad intelligence, dear Mr Wilson, that poor Sonder is dead! ¶ Sonder died on 21 November 1881. ¶  ¶ He was the ¶  ¶ dearest ¶  ¶ of my scientific friends, wit...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">82.01.17a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Thomas Wilson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">V81/11657, unit<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                    style="font-weight: bold; background-color: #FFFF00; ">get number</seg>, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">NOTE: this letter is amongst 1883 letters.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>17/1/82</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The last mail brought me the sad intelligence, dear Mr Wilson, that poor Sonder is dead!<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sonder died on 21 November 1881.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>He was the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">dearest</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of my scientific friends, with whom I was in communication about plants since my<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">boyhood</hi>
               </seg>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This mournful occurrence made me ask, whether I could have a short interview with the hon. J. M. Grant, as I am still most eager, that his grand collections of dried plants should be secured for the colony.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to T. Wilson, 26 December 1881<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1527FF; ">asked for a meeting with James Grant to explain his case.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Kindly say, when it would be a good day &amp; hour to wait on the Chief Secretary regarding this subject, as I ought to write to the mourning widow more fully by next mail. In the fever dreams of his last short illness he was speaking again &amp; again about the seaweeds, concerning which til his sudden death I was in constant communication with my poor generous and clever friend.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>annotation: 'Can [it] be entertained JMG 18/1/82'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">A<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">response</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was sent to M on 21</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>January 1882 (letter not found)</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">saying what?Any indication in the annotations?</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1527FF; ">.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1527FF; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1527FF; ">T. Wilson to M, 21</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1527FF; ">January 1882 (in this edition as 82-01-21a) reported that 'the Chief Secretary declines to entertain the proposal'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>T. Wilson,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>26 December 1881,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to T. Wilson,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1 January<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1884,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>are filed with this letter. The file also contains an obituary of Sonder published in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Chemist and druggist</seg>, January 1882. This includes: 'Since that time [the death of William Harvey] his attention was particularly directed to the investigations of Australian Algae, concerning which he was, since 1848, in very frequent communication with Baron von Muëller'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #1527FF; ">See Short (1990).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
